<body>
  <h1>Create a Simple REST API with Express.js</h1>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>1. Setting Up the API</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Create a basic Express.js application</li>
      <li>Define a route for the root URL ("/") that returns a "Hello, World!" message</li>
      <li>Implement error handling for invalid routes</li>
      <li>Set up middleware (e.g., <code>express.json()</code>) for parsing request bodies</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>2. Creating Routes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>GET /items - Retrieve all items</li>
      <li>GET /items/:id - Retrieve a single item by ID</li>
      <li>POST /items - Create a new item</li>
      <li>PUT /items/:id - Update an item by ID</li>
      <li>DELETE /items/:id - Delete an item by ID</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>3. Data Management</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Create a simple in-memory data store (array)</li>
      <li>Each item should have: id, name, description</li>
      <li>Implement validation for incoming data</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>4. Error Handling</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Return appropriate error responses (400, 404, 500)</li>
      <li>Return meaningful error messages</li>
      <li>Validate request parameters and body</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>5. Testing</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide sample API requests using tools like Postman</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Submission Requirements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Working Express.js app with all routes</li>
      <li>README.md with setup and documentation</li>
      <li>Example requests and expected responses</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</body>
